results.name: Decimal expansion of the radius of convergence of the generating function of A000598, the number of rooted ternary trees of n vertices.
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge University Press, 2003, Section 5.6 Otter's tree enumeration constants, p. 298.
link: Philippe Flajolet and Robert Sedgewick, Analytic Combinatorics, 2009; p. 478.
mathematica: digits = 97; m = 2 digits + 10; For[gf = 0; i = 0, i <= m, i++, gf = Series[1 + x*(gf^3/6 + (gf /. x -> x^2)*gf/2 + (gf /. x -> x^3)/3), {x, 0, m + 1}] // Normal];

g[r_] := Module[{r2, r3, X, ym}, r2 = gf /. x -> r^2; r3 = gf /. x -> r^3; X[y_] = (y - 1)/(y^3/6 + r2*y/2 + r3/3); ym = y /. FindRoot[X'[y] == 0, {y, 2}, WorkingPrecision -> digits + 5]; X[ym]]; rho = FixedPoint[g, 1/3, SameTest -> (Abs[#1 - #2] < 10^-digits &)]; RealDigits[rho, 10, digits] // First
